In [6]:
def show_img(img):
  if type(img) is list:
    tam = len(img)
    if tam % 3 == 0:
      lin, col = tam//3, 3
    elif tam < 3:
      lin, col = 1, tam
    else:
      lin, col = (tam//3) + 1, 3
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(lin, col)
    for i in range(lin):
      for j in range(col):
        if lin != 1:
          axes[i, j].imshow(img[tam-1])
          axes[i, j].axis('off')
        else:
          axes[j].imshow(img[tam-1])
          axes[j].axis('off')
        tam -= 1
  else:
    plt.imshow(img)
  plt.axis('off')
  plt.show()
